description: Learn how to make healthier chicken nuggets with this easy recipe. Cooked in an air fryer, these golden nuggets make a great addition to kids' lunch boxes.
keywords: Kids,Air fryer,Seafood free,Tree nut free,Healthier Easier,Low sugar,High protein,High fibre,Mince,Chicken,Peanut free
name: Air-fryer Nuggets Lunch Boxes Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 1 large Lebanese cucumber, cut into batons

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat air fryer on 200Â°C for 4 minutes. Meanwhile, place bread into a food processor. Process for 15 seconds until fine crumbs form. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.

Place carrot in food processor. Process for 15 seconds or until finely chopped. Add chicken, egg and half of the breadcrumbs. Season with pepper. Pulse for 10 seconds or until just combined. Using damp hands, form tablespoonfuls of the chicken mixture into nuggets, then coat in remaining breadcrumbs.

Spray half the nuggets with oil and place, in a single layer, in air-fryer basket. Cook for 8 minutes, turning halfway, or until golden and cooked through. Repeat with remaining nuggets and oil. Serve nuggets in lunch boxes with cucumber, cheese and kiwi fruit.
